Major General Allen Batschelet says that 10 percent of young men and women who sign up to join the Army are currently refused because they are too heavy . 
  He warns that as many as half of young Americans will be overweight by the end of the decade and the military will be unable to recruit enough qualified soldiers . 
  Army recruiters are having to act like the trainers on NBC's The Biggest Loser  . 
  Of the 195,000 recruits in 2014 only 72,000 qualified . 
 